	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=17094><span id=Sage>Kneesmasher</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>397 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.69]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Dalantia<br><br>At level 17, Mistmoore will prove risky for you without a good and strong group to help you.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is really no comparison between Unrest and Mistmoore. Mistmoore being FAR more difficult and risky.  I see level 50's fleeing Mistmoore for the zone. That doesn't happen much in Unrest.  <br><br>At level 17 you are pushing it to be in Unrest except for the yard trash and such.  Trains will undoubtedly wipe you out, as you have no doubt witnessed already. Don't let it sour you on the zone. You are simply not high enough to be there to hunt the zone effectively.  Go back at level 22 when you have your Invis to Undead and you will find it to be much more accomodating.<br><br>I'm not saying you shouldn't go to either place. I love Mistmoore as everyone who reads this site knows, and I have spent countless time in Unrest as well. But I do say go to MM with Caution. It is not to be taken lightly, even at level 37, let alone level 17. I would certainly wait til at least level 20 before even sticking my nose into MM.<br><br>If you are having trouble at level 17 getting XP, try Crushbone. If that isn't to your liking, try Chessboard if you want to fight Undead.<br><br>Good luck! Just My Humble Opinion.....<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>37th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"<br></p>&nbsp;<br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>Dwarven Knight<br>Torvonnilous Server<br><br>"Never Mistake Kindness for Weakness"</td></td></tr>
